	(text "Figure 8 shows how two I2S Microphones can be connected on a single I2S bus. R41-R44 are included to dampen or terminate their\nrespective traces. If the traces are electrically long then they should be controlled impedance traces with impedance in the 50-120 Ohm\nrange. Traces are considered electrically long when the length of the trace (in inches) is greater than 2 times the rise/fall time (in nS).\nEven if the traces are not electrically long, R41-R44 can be used as dampening resistors (27-51 Ohms) to improve signal integrity by\nreducing overshoots and ringing caused by stray inductance and capacitance. In either case, R41-R44 are to be placed as close as\npossible to the device that drives the trace (signal source). The decoupling capacitors (C32-33, and C34-35) are most effective if the\ntrace inductance between the capacitor and microphone is minimized. This can be accomplished by using short, wide traces. If a\nground plane is used under the microphone, then connect the capacitor ground pads directly to the plane with vias without any trace\nused."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 393.446 37.846 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
			)
		)
		(uuid "6769b7c9-79a3-4baf-ac4d-ed694d4913cd")
	)
